From: Cole Leavitt <cole@unwrap.rs>
Subject: nss-gk-api: explicitly allowlist SECItemType for clang>=22

bindings.toml lists SECItemType only under the `enums` section, which calls
bindgen's constified_enum_module() — that configures formatting but does not
add to the allowlist. With older clang/libclang versions, SECItemType was
auto-included as a transitive dependency of the allowlisted SECItemStr
struct (its `type` field). Newer libclang (>=22) no longer auto-includes
typedef enums when only the parent struct is allowlisted.

Result: lib.rs:52 fails to import nss_prelude::SECItemType, breaking the
nss-gk-api crate compile during `force-cargo-library-build`.

Fix: explicitly add SECItemType to the `types` allowlist. Harmless on older
clang and required on clang>=22. Mozilla CI uses pinned clang so they don't
hit this; downstream builders against system clang do.

--- a/third_party/rust/nss-gk-api/bindings/bindings.toml
+++ b/third_party/rust/nss-gk-api/bindings/bindings.toml
@@ -33,6 +33,7 @@
     "SECItem",
     "SECItemArray",
     "SECItemStr",
+    "SECItemType",
     "SECStatus",
 ]
 functions = [
